{"word":"ἀκίς","slug":"ἀκίς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀκίς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἀκή</el> I\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a point, the barb</i> of an arrow or hook, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:—<i>an arrow, dart</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>πόθων ἀκίδες</el> <i>the stings</i> of desire, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}